Editorial Escudo de Oro | 1982 | ISBN: 8437809266 | English | 100 pages | PDF | 9.2 MB

One kind of painting was practised before the appearance of Picasso. After the revolutionary intervention in the world of plastic arts of the genius from Malaga, there was another type of painting. As the author of Guernica himself said, &quot;We now know that art is not truth. Art is a lie that makes us realise truth, at least the truth which is given us to understand (...) The artist must find the way of convincing the public of the entire veracity of his lies.&quot;
